Good to know that my town has this place!

name: Nasi Jinggo - Bu Jero
address: Jl. Imam Bonjol No.3, Kediri, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Worth the price! You can get a full meal for under 25k rupiah. You can get nasi Jinggo for 7k each and add some topping (satay or crisps) separately.
review 2: Packaged rice is at 6000 each, open it on the spot to see whether the portion is enough and many fried items to add to your plate as additional side dishes, from 2500 onwards. Orange juice 6000, coffee 5000. Meal for 2 plus drinks around 40000. Special dish is Sate Kukul: escargot satay, spicy tapioca and Balinese rujak.
review 3: Good place for a local meal, try Kangkong plecing, which is green veg in spicy peanut sauce. Otherwise most side dishes are fried items. Good meal, but maybe not enough green veg. Payment is honesty based, you tally up what you eat and pay instead of them keeping track.
review 4: Many kind of menu, portion of wrapped rice is okey (not too much or little), price is good enough but little bit expensive for beverage
review 5: A great place to have your meal, its really cheap and the food is graded high in my opinion, I love the arrangement and unique setup in the restaurant.
